message: “Awareness is not enough for us, we want to stop this,” said District Attorney Summer Stephan, one of a half-dozen leaders who addressed the gathering.

data.description: Dozens of marchers strode through Balboa Park Saturday afternoon to draw attention to human trafficking, a crime that claims an estimated average of 5,400 victims annually in San Diego County.
data.title: Activists, leaders call for continued fight against human trafficking
